only position size and reward

00:56:27.130 --> 00:56:32.730
to risk, exit strategies, then
you're an expert investor.

00:56:32.730 --> 00:56:35.760
So there are two actions
that I recommend.

00:56:35.760 --> 00:56:38.390
You can do these today,
do these tonight.

00:56:38.390 --> 00:56:40.630
The first is, define
your strategy.

00:56:40.630 --> 00:56:42.920
It should have three part.

00:56:42.920 --> 00:56:45.590
What kind of companies
are you looking to buy?

00:56:45.590 --> 00:56:47.644
What things are you
going to think about

00:56:47.644 --> 00:56:48.810
while you own that business?

00:56:48.810 --> 00:56:50.180
In other words, how are
you going to keep up

00:56:50.180 --> 00:56:51.320
to date with the moves.

00:56:51.320 --> 00:56:56.470
And then, what are the exit
strategies for you to sell?

00:56:56.470 --> 00:56:59.056
Put this in writing,
because if you

00:56:59.056 --> 00:57:00.680
don't put it in
writing then you really

00:57:00.680 --> 00:57:02.630
don't have an exit strategy.

00:57:02.630 --> 00:57:04.370
You don't have an
investment strategy.

00:57:04.370 --> 00:57:06.590
The second thing
I mentioned to do

00:57:06.590 --> 00:57:07.960
is create an investment journal.

00:57:07.960 --> 00:57:10.850
So if open up
Google Docs, Excel,

00:57:10.850 --> 00:57:12.480
and every time
you buy a stock, I

00:57:12.480 --> 00:57:15.366
want you to put in the
company's name, the symbol,

00:57:15.366 --> 00:57:18.510
the number of shares you
buy and the purchase price.

00:57:18.510 --> 00:57:22.360
I want you put in your estimate
of the intrinsic value.

00:57:22.360 --> 00:57:25.820
And then I want you put in-- you
can have a formula that tells

00:57:25.820 --> 00:57:28.310
you the reward to risk ratio.

00:57:28.310 --> 00:57:31.650
It should be at
least, what, three.

00:57:31.650 --> 00:57:32.340
OK.

00:57:32.340 --> 00:57:36.632
Paul Tudor Jones, do you
know what he looks for?

00:57:36.632 --> 00:57:37.504
Five.

00:57:37.504 --> 00:57:41.900
So if you want be a
billionaire, look for fives.

00:57:41.900 --> 00:57:46.420
And then when it comes to
time to sell your position,

00:57:46.420 --> 00:57:50.500
make a couple of
other data entries--

00:57:50.500 --> 00:57:54.850
the sell price, the date,
what your thesis is.

00:57:54.850 --> 00:57:57.430
Maybe the company broke
the 200-day moving average.

00:57:57.430 --> 00:58:00.950
Maybe the thesis is not as
attractive as-- whatever

00:58:00.950 --> 00:58:05.180
the reason is, just make a
note of that information.

00:58:05.180 --> 00:58:09.200
Then you can compare your
actual reward to risk ratio

00:58:09.200 --> 00:58:11.155
to your expected reward ratio.

00:58:11.155 --> 00:58:16.700
