01:11:46.950 --> 01:11:48.570
I want a clarification--
you say you

01:11:48.570 --> 01:11:51.760
want to sell when it drops
below a certain percentage.

01:11:51.760 --> 01:11:53.970
Nowadays the market even
fluctuates so much, right,

01:11:53.970 --> 01:11:55.410
based on given
news and something.

01:11:55.410 --> 01:11:56.826
A lot of people,
even pundits have

01:11:56.826 --> 01:11:59.217
said that certain good stocks,
if you have it-- example,

01:11:59.217 --> 01:12:00.800
Microsoft or [INAUDIBLE]
or something,

01:12:00.800 --> 01:12:02.900
they could fluctuate
10% in a given week,

01:12:02.900 --> 01:12:04.720
and you could be missing
out on 10 baggers

01:12:04.720 --> 01:12:08.950
100 baggers if you act on
this volatility, right.

01:12:08.950 --> 01:12:14.542
So when you say you sell on
a certain percentage down,

01:12:14.542 --> 01:12:16.000
are you discounting
the volatility?

01:12:16.000 --> 01:12:21.130
Or if your fund-- or if your
stock is 10% below the market,

01:12:21.130 --> 01:12:24.060
we just-- let's say, the
S&amp;P today has opened up 5%

01:12:24.060 --> 01:12:26.280
and my stock went 10%.

01:12:26.280 --> 01:12:29.600
So I'm only down 5% or am I
really down 10% [INAUDIBLE]?

01:12:32.620 --> 01:12:34.370
HEWITT HEISERMAN:
That's a great question.

01:12:34.370 --> 01:12:37.090
I didn't address it.

01:12:37.090 --> 01:12:38.610
That's something
for you to answer.

01:12:38.610 --> 01:12:40.085
Do you want to
sell your positions

01:12:40.085 --> 01:12:42.990
if they're falling at
the same rate of decline

01:12:42.990 --> 01:12:45.300
as the overall market?

01:12:45.300 --> 01:12:52.250
Or are you looking for say
some decline that's above

01:12:52.250 --> 01:12:54.130
and beyond what the
market decline is?

01:12:54.130 --> 01:12:56.675
And I don't know the
answer to that for you

01:12:56.675 --> 01:12:59.870
because these are personal
decisions that have to make.

01:12:59.870 --> 01:13:04.380
What I'm trying to
say is, in my case,

01:13:04.380 --> 01:13:05.835
I recognize one
of my limitations

01:13:05.835 --> 01:13:13.330
is that getting emotional about
a position that's down 25%,

01:13:13.330 --> 01:13:16.240
and I don't want to be
in that position again.

01:13:16.240 --> 01:13:18.360
And so I created
some strategies so

01:13:18.360 --> 01:13:22.070
that that's not going to occur.

01:13:22.070 --> 01:13:24.957
So you may decide that
you'll put up with the market

01:13:24.957 --> 01:13:26.540
volatility, you're
just going to focus

01:13:26.540 --> 01:13:28.720
on the company-specific
volatility.

01:13:28.720 --> 01:13:33.440
And that may be an
excellent approach.

